attr.attrdefs: For Interstate highways (rt_no_prfx=I), this attribute can be decoded to indicate mile markers. Segment numbers ending in 1 or 0 are mileposts (for example, a seg_no of 0221 or 0220 indicates the 22nd mile). Segment numbers ending in 4 or 5 indicate a half-mile. Interstates are generally measured South to North or West to East. Even numbered segments indicate the measured direction of travel while odd numbered segments indicate the other side of the highway. Segments numbers ending with other digits are county line breaks.
